{
  "texts": [
    "They are outside of the province of individual human agency since, at a minimum, this wider structure involves the interference patterns generated by multiple interacting streams of agential involvement.",
    "On the other hand, the internal teleological microstructure of the act, laid bare in the series (A)-(D), is a happening that can be ascribed to the agent only.",
    "17 Pump handles being manipulated, water being pumped out of faucets: these are things that we can recognise as belonging to the class of what individual agents accomplish through the exercise of their practi- 16 Of course, there is much more to say about deviant causal chains than this brief summary of an Anscombean response can address (for helpful recent discussion of deviant causal chains in a range of contexts, see Ward 2024).",
    "And, as an anonymous reviewer worries, the Anscombean solution can look problematically circular.",
    "I address this worry later in the main text (§5.4), building on the considerations about teleology and normativity introduced above (§2.2)."
  ]
}